## Reflection

This project challenged me in ways I did not expect. I assumed that downloading and setting up the project files would be the most difficult part, but the compression and archiving tasks exposed several gaps in my understanding of command options and compression methods.

The biggest lesson was the importance of consulting documentation rather than relying on memory. Most of my mistakes came from missing or incorrect flags rather than misunderstanding the overall objective.

I also noticed that my troubleshooting process is becoming more structured. Rather than repeatedly guessing commands, I increasingly relied on the man pages to verify available options and understand why commands were failing.

Although the project was relatively short, it was a productive exercise that reinforced file management, compression techniques, troubleshooting skills, and the habit of using documentation to solve problems independently.
